Package: OptSLDP
Title: OptSLDP: An Optimized Selective Linkage Disequilibrium Pruning Pipeline
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Félicien", "Akohoue", role = c("aut", "cre"),
    email = "akohoue.f@gmail.com")
Description: Implements OptSLDP, an optimized and extended version of the
    Selective Linkage Disequilibrium Pruning (SLDP) pipeline for genomic
    prediction panel construction. OptSLDP improves on the original SLDP
    algorithm (Zhu et al., 2023) by introducing chunked memory-safe genotype
    reading, explicit per-chromosome garbage collection, multi-trait union
    protection, and covariate-adjusted marginal screening. Supports three input
    formats (numeric dosage, HapMap, VCF), three candidate selection modes
    (p-value, z-score, PVE), positional and LD-based expansion of protected
    marker sets, and chromosome-wise background pruning. Includes stream-cleaning of malformed genotype files for all supported
    formats. Scales automatically from small panels (in-memory) to
    whole-genome sequencing data with more than 10 million SNPs via a
    GDS/SNPRelate disk-backed backend. References:
    Zhu et al. (2023) <doi:10.1186/s12711-023-00843-w>;
    Akohoue et al. (2026) <doi:10.1007/s00122-026-05159-z>.
